Hello Adrienne, and all my fellow yogis. This my third 30 day yoga journey, and my first time I am adding a comment. My mind wants to judge myself, and apologize for that, but my heart says there is no place for self judgement. So with that I want to say thank you Adrienne for who you are and what you do.                                        I have wanted to become a yoga teacher for many years, but honestly haven‚Äôt had the spare money, and more then that, I haven‚Äôt believed in myself enough. So at the end of last November, my wife inspired me to go on a one year yoga journey. She challenged me to do yoga everyday for one year, and to study all of the components of the true practice of yoga. She also challenged me to, at the end of my six months of daily yoga practice, to start teaching yoga, to my friends. So that is my journey. I am on day 112. 112 straight days!                                                    I never thought I could do anything like this before, but for some reason it felt right this time. I always looked at yoga from a different way...wanting to get strong and have a good physic, but when my wife gave me this challenge, I had such a different vision of my yoga practice. It has been a beautiful journey, and again I want to say thank you Adrienne. üôèüôèüôè
